\"login\": \"ValWood\"\n23:       },\n24:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n25:       \"body\": \"I can add \\n\\n'biosynthetic process'\\n and ('has primary output' some 'terreic acid')\\n\\nbut I'm not sure how to get 'terreic acid' to be recognized. This should then locate any missing parents.\",\n26:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-01-19T17:42:07Z\",\n27:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n28:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n29:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n30:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n31:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31114#issuecomment-3769517182\",\n32:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n33:     },\n34:     {\n35:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7g9EbT\",\n36:       \"author\": {\n37:         \"login\": \"ValWood\"\n38:       },\n39:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n40:       \"body\": \"How do I get CHEBI:156546 to be recognized for logical derf?\",\n41:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-01-20T17:30:25Z\",\n42:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n43:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n44:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n45:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n46:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31114#issuecomment-3774105299\",\n47:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n48:     },\n49:     {\n50:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7g9VRV\",\n51:       \"author\": {\n52:         \"login\": \"balhoff\"\n53:       },\n54:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n55:       \"body\": \"@ValWood I added [terreate](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/chebi/CHEBI:233617) in #31385. That seems to be the pH 7.3 version. Once that is merged I can build a new CHEBI import.\",\n56:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-01-20T17:47:06Z\",\n57:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n58:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n59:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n60:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n61:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31114#issuecomment-3774174293\",\n62:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n63:     },\n64:     {\n65:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7g-28n\",\n66:       \"author\": {\n67:         \"login\": \"balhoff\"\n68:       },\n69:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n70:       \"body\": \"@ValWood you can look for the term now.\",\n71:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-01-20T19:27:08Z\",\n72:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n73:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n74:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n75:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n76:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31114#issuecomment-3774574375\",\n77:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n78:     },\n79:     {\n80:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7rFUMs\",\n81:       \"author\": {\n82:         \"login\": \"ValWood\"\n83:       },\n84:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n85:       \"body\": \"I added this, but I just found\\nGO:0140880  terrein biosynthetic process\\nhttps://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/23601\\n\\n@Antonialock  how are these related?  AI says  terrein is an intermediate in terreic acid biosynthesis.\\nAny insight? I wonder if we really need both terms if they describe the same pathway?\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n86:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-02-23T10:52:34Z\",\n87:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n88:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n89:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n90:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n91:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31114#issuecomment-3944039212\",\n92:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n93:     },\n94:     {\n95:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7rHsrp\",\n96:       \"author\": {\n97:         \"login\": \"Antonialock\"\n98:       },\n99:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n100:       \"body\": \"i think this looks ok\\n\\nit was a while since I looked at this but claude output:\\nTerrein and terreic acid are both secondary metabolites produced by Aspergillus terreus (and some related fungi), but they are distinct compounds with different biosynthetic origins.\\n\\n<img width=\\\"716\\\" height=\\\"346\\\" alt=\\\"Image\\\" src=\\\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0a5ce089-f398-4574-bef1-3158ce42f6c6\\\" />\\n\\nSo despite both being polyketides from the same organism, they arise from distinct gene clusters, use different PKS enzymes, proceed through different intermediates, and yield structurally unrelated end products. The terreic acid pathway is more thoroughly characterized at the molecular level, while the terrein pathway was discovered more recently and still has some gaps\",\n101:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-02-23T13:02:12Z\",\n102:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n103:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n104:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n105:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n106:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31114#issuecomment-3944663785\",\n107:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n108:     },\n109:     {\n110:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7rJEpG\",\n111:       \"author\": {\n112:         \"login\": \"Antonialock\"\n113:       },\n114:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n115:       \"body\": \"the genes are definitely different!\",\n116:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-02-23T14:15:54Z\",\n117:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n118:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n119:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n120:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n121:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31114#issuecomment-3945024070\",\n122:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n123:     },\n124:     {\n125:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABAw_AzA\",\n126:       \"author\": {\n127:         \"login\": \"ValWood\"\n128:       },\n129:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n130:       \"body\": \" @dragon-ai-agent  please implement  new term request \\\"terreic acid biosynthetic process\\\" as previously (I closed the previous pull request due to a conflict)\",\n131:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-29T18:14:08Z\",\n132:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\