yms. The logical definition still uses `CHEBI:233617 ! terreate` (the pH 7.3 form) — this matches the GO chemical-entity convention of biologist-friendly label + pH 7.3 CHEBI in the logical def (cf. the L-histidine exemplar). No new IDs were minted; this is a rename, so `created_by`/`creation_date` are unchanged.\\n\\n`make travis_build` passes cleanly.\\n\\nIf you'd prefer the labels stay as `terreate ...` (i.e. the chemistry name), let me know and I'll close the PR. Otherwise this should close out the original request.\\n\\n---\\n🤖 **Generated by @dragon-ai-agent**\\n- Model: `claude-opus-4-7`\\n- Agent harness: claude-code\\n- Triggered by: @ValWood\\n- Run: [View workflow run](https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/actions/runs/25125987501)\",\n168:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-29T18:32:12Z\",\n169:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n170:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n171:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n172:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n173:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31114#issuecomment-4346463264\",\n174:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n175:     },\n176:     {\n177:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABAxLSIQ\",\n178:       \"author\": {\n179:         \"login\": \"ValWood\"\n180:       },\n181:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n182:       \"body\": \"@Antonialock  please check if this is correct?\\n\",\n183:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-29T18:40:29Z\",\n184:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n185:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n186:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n187:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n188:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31114#issuecomment-4346532385\",\n189:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n190:     },\n191:     {\n192:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABA0dYUw\",\n193:       \"author\": {\n194:         \"login\": \"ValWood\"\n195:       },\n196:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n197:       \"body\": \"@Antonialock  this was in 